To specify and restrict the size of a cell in the model list view of Flask Admin, you can use the `column_formatters` attribute in the model view class. Here's an example of how you can set the width of a specific column in your Flask Admin list view:

```python
from flask_admin.model import typefmt

class CustomAdminView(ModelView):
    column_formatters = {
        'column_name': typefmt.fmt_std_width(100)  # Set width of the column to 100px
    }
```

In this example, replace `'column_name'` with the name of the column for which you want to set the width, and `100` with the desired width in pixels. You can also adjust the width value to suit your specific requirements.

By using `column_formatters`, you can customize the appearance of individual columns in the list view and enforce a specific width for the cells.

