To set the height of a cell in an HTML table using Flask-Admin, you can override the CSS styles for the table cells in the list view of your model. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to achieve this:

1. Create a custom template for the Flask-Admin list view for your model. You can do this by extending the base template provided by Flask-Admin.

```html
<!-- custom_list.html -->
{% extends 'admin/model/list.html' %}

{% block head %}
    {{ super() }}
    <style>
        .table td.custom-cell {
            height: 50px; /* Set the desired cell height */
        }
    </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block list_row %}
    <tr>
        {% for column in list_columns %}
            <td class="custom-cell">{{ column_fmt(row, column) }}</td>
        {% endfor %}
    </tr>
{% endblock %}
```

2. Customize the `list_view` method of your ModelView class to use the custom template.

```python
from flask_admin.contrib.sqla import ModelView

class CustomModelView(ModelView):
    list_template = 'custom_list.html'
```

3. Ensure that Flask-Admin is configured to load the custom template.

```python
from flask_admin import Admin

admin = Admin(app, template_mode='bootstrap4')
admin.add_view(CustomModelView(ModelClass))
```

By creating a custom template that overrides the CSS styles for `<td>` elements, you can effectively set the height of cells in the HTML table displayed in Flask-Admin. Make sure to adjust the custom styles in the template to suit your specific design requirements.

